name: src/collection.js
Collection
description: The Collection object.

name: constructor
description: The collection constructor.

params.name: items
params.description: the array to collect.

return.description: A Collection object.

name: items
description: The internal array.

name: length
description: The length of the array.

name: add
description: Adds an item to the collection.

params.name: item
params.description: the item to be added.

name: all
description: Gets the collected elements in an array.

return.description: the internal array.

name: average
description:
Gets the average value of the array or a property or a callback return value.
If no property is provided: it will calculate the average value of the array (Numeric array).
If property is a string: it will calculate the average value of that property for all
 objects in the array.
If Property is a callback: the the averaging will use the value returned instead.

params.name: property
params.description:
The property name or the callback function.
defaults to null.

return.description: The average value.

name: chunk
description: Chunks the collection into a new collection with equal length arrays as its items.

params.name: size
params.description: the size of each chunk.

return.description: the new collection.

name: collect
description: Static constructor. Will transform a string to array of strings.

params.name: collectable
params.description: the array or the string to wrapped in a collection.

return.description: A collection that wraps the collectable items.

name: concat
description: Concatnates the collection with an array or another collection.

params.name: collection
params.description: the array or the collection to be concatenated with.

return.description: concatenated collection.

name: count
description: Gets the number of items in the collection.

return.description: Number of items in the collection.

name: each
description: Executes a callback for each element in the collection.

params.name: callback
params.description: the callback to be excuted for each item.

return.description: this

name: filter
description: Filters the collection using a predicate (callback that returns a boolean).

params.name: callback
params.description: A function that returns a boolean expression.

return.description: Filtered collection.

name: find
description: Gets an element at a specified index.

params.name: index
params.description: the index of the item.

return.description: the item at that index.

name: first
description: Gets the first element satisfying a critera.

params.name: callback
params.description: the predicate (callback) that will be applied on items.

return.description: the first item to satisfy the critera.

name: flatten
description: Flattens the collection elements.

params.name: deep
params.description: recursively flatten the items (multi-level).

return.description: the flattened collection.

name: keys
description: Gets the collection elements keys in a new collection.

return.description: The keys collection.

name: last
description: Gets the last element to satisfy a callback.

params.name: callback
params.description: the predicate to be checked on all elements.

return.description: The last element in the collection that satisfies the predicate.

name: map
description: Maps each element using a mapping function and collects the mapped items.

params.name: callback
params.description: the mapping function.

return.description: collection containing the mapped items.

name: pluck
description: Extracts a property from the objects in the collection.

params.name: property
params.description: the name of the property to be extracted.

return.description: A collection with the extracted items.

name: push
description: Adds an element to the collection.

params.name: item
params.description: the item to be added.

name: reduce
description: Reduces the collection to a single value using a reducing function.

params.name: callback
params.description: the reducing function.

params.name: initial
params.description: initial value.

return.description: The reduced results.

name: reject
description: Removes the elements that do not satisfy the predicate.

params.name: callback
params.description: the predicate used on each item.

return.description: A collection without the rejected elements.

name: reverse
description: Reverses the collection order.

return.description: A new collection with the reversed order.

name: skip
description: Skips a specified number of elements.

params.name: count
params.description: the number of items to be skipped.

return.description: A collection without the skipped items.

name: slice
description: Slices the collection starting from a specific index and ending at a specified index.

params.name: start
params.description: The zero-based starting index.

params.name: end
params.description: The zero-based ending index.

return.description: A collection with the sliced items.

name: stringify
description: Stringifies the collection using JSON.stringify API.

return.description: The stringified value.

name: sum
description: Sums the values of the array, or the properties, or the result of the callback.

params.name: property
params.description: the property to be summed.

return.description: The sum of values used in the summation.

name: take
description: Gets a new collection with the number of specified items from the begining or the end.

params.name: count
params.description: the number of items to take. Takes from end if negative.

return.description: A collection with the taken items.

name: where
description: Filters the collection using a callback or equality comparison to a property in each item.

params.name: callback
params.description: The callback to be used to filter the collection.

params.name: value
params.description: The value to be compared.

return.description: A collection with the filtered items.

name: zip
description: Pairs each item in the collection with another array item in the same index.

params.name: array
params.description: the array to be paired with.

return.description: A collection with the paired items.
